				"default": false,
				"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">You soften a patch of dry ground you can see within range into a horrible caustic mire. The spell’s area becomes difficult terrain. A creature that enters the area for the first time on its turn or begins its turn in the area must make a Strength saving throw or be grappled (escape DC equal to your spell save DC) and take 2d6 points of acid damage. A creature that begins its turn grappled by the spell also takes 2d6 points of acid damage. </p><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-fec4f85f-7fff-f8f5-0d13-3d645accc826\">Cast at Higher Levels. </strong>The acid damage increases by 1d6 for each spell slot level above 3rd.</p>",
